biography: Carla Hustedt leads the [Ethics of Algorithms](https://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/en/our-projects/ethics-of-algorithms/) project of the Bertelsmann Stiftung. In the project, she takes a close look at the societal consequences of algorithmic decision-making, hoping to contribute to the development of technology that can ultimately facilitate greater social inclusion. Previously she founded the German-Ghanaian human rights NGO “Boa Nnipa”, managed the office of a German MP and consulted international clients from the technology sector on their public affairs strategies. Carla holds a Master in Public Policy from the Hertie School of Governance and a Master in Public Administration from the London School of Economics, with a focus on e-governance and behavioural economics. She is particularly proud of her first job: formatting floppy disk in her father’s laptop store.
